		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Charleston</placeName> <date>12 April 1852</date></p>
			<p>My dear friend</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">I have recd several apologies from<lb/> you for not writing which are unnecessary as I<lb/> know you have been very busy since your return<lb/> I have just learned that <persName>Revrd Ellis Lyons</persName> has been<lb/> supoened<add>&#63;</add> to attend a trial of <persName>Rev Henry</persName> vs <persName>I Leeser</persName><lb/> for slander. I had some inkling of <del>it but</del> the intention<lb/> but did not suppose it would be put in execution&#44;&#8212;<lb/>I write now merely to suggest that you will keep<lb/> perfectly quiet and not commit yourself by any remarks<lb/> in <placeName>Phil<hi rend="sup">a</hi></placeName>. <persName>Mr Lyons</persName> is <hi rend="underline">no</hi> evidence&#44; as <hi rend="underline">you</hi> never<lb/> told <persName>Mr Lyons</persName> any thing about <persName>Mr Henry</persName>&#44; <persName>Mr Lyons</persName><lb/> heard it from a third or probably a fourth person<lb/> which is <hi rend="underline">no evidence at all</hi>. I suppose you have<lb/> procured counsel &#38; <del>and</del> be guided entirely by him.<lb/> I am sorry our good friend <persName>SS.</persName> is not in <placeName>Phila</placeName> as<lb/> he would have probably advised you as to how you<lb/> are to proceed. Let me know the particulars and if<lb/> I can be of any use to you in any way&#63; You<lb/> will have to summon <persName><hi rend="underline">Dr Raphael</hi></persName> and have a<lb/> commission sent to examine the parties in <placeName>Cincinatti</placeName>&#8212;<lb/>&#8212;your <sic>defence</sic> will be however <hi rend="underline">not to prove</hi> your<lb/> remark <hi rend="underline">true</hi>&#44; as the greater the truth the greater<lb/> the Libel&#44; but to make <hi rend="underline">him prove</hi> that you said<lb/> any thing <hi rend="underline">libellous</hi>.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">The Occident is at hand and Jerusalem has been<lb/> my companion among my leisure hours. I have</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>recd <persName>Samuels</persName> Translation&#44; and I like yours<lb/> better as the language is more eupho<add>&#63;</add> and<lb/> smoother than his. I cannot tell of course how<lb/> the original is but should judge it to be a close<lb/> translation from its resemblance in many particulars<lb/> to the one by <persName>Samuels</persName>. I am sure the public<lb/> would rather have Jerusalem than 3 Nos of the Occident<lb/>&#8212;When are we to have the <date>Apl</date> No.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Do you think you acted prudently in publishing<lb/> <persName>Mr Poznanski&#39;s</persName> letter. I have heard but <hi rend="underline">one</hi><lb/> opinion about it here&#44; which is unfavorable.<lb/> I hope it will not injure you&#44; and I <sic>dont</sic><lb/> see how it will benefit you&#44; I only write this to<lb/> let your public opinion in this quarter.</p>
			<p>I have heard it remarked that <persName>Mr Leeser</persName><lb/> denounced <persName>Dr Raphael</persName> for giving <sic>recommendary</sic><lb/> letters to <persName>Rubenstein</persName> for KKBE&#44; and<lb/> <persName>Mr Leeser</persName> has done the same thing himself<lb/> <persName>Mr Moise</persName> told me that the <add>&#63;</add> of KKBE<lb/> have a letter from you speaking in the highest<lb/> terms of a <persName>Mr Myer</persName> or <persName>Mayers</persName>&#44; formerly<lb/> a pupil of <persName>Dr Lennialhas<add>&#63;</add></persName>. Write me if it is<lb/> so&#8212;and if you know any thing of <persName>Mr Myers</persName><lb/> principles. I understand that he has written to the<lb/> Trustees that he believes and approves of the bible<lb/> <hi rend="underline">subject however to criticism</hi>&#44; I also learn<lb/> that <persName>Poznanski</persName> has written to <persName>Mr Myer</persName> that he<lb/> <hi rend="underline">rejoices</hi> in his principles&#8212;there was to be a<lb/> meeting last night&#44; on the subject&#44; and</p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p>your favorable opinion will have done much to<lb/> gain him the office&#44; if he is elected.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Write one a letter that I can<lb/> <hi rend="underline">show</hi> to <persName>Mr Moise</persName> who wishes to know if <hi rend="underline">you</hi><lb/> approve of his religious opinions &#38; principles.</p>
			<p>I hope you are well. Dear <persName>Sarah</persName><lb/> and little ones are in tolerable health.<lb/> <persName>Dr Eckman</persName> is in <placeName>Augusta</placeName>&#44; he<lb/> will return shortly. Kind regards<lb/> to all friends.</p>
          <p rend="indent(6)">Yours Truly</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">J. N. Carvalho</persName></p>
		<pb n="4"/>
			<p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p>Editor Occident</p>
			<p><placeName>Walnut near 13th</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          
